President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key positions in his administration. Michael George DeSombre, of Illinois, is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Kingdom of Thailand. DeSombre is a partner at Sullivan & Cromwell, LLP law firm and serves on the board of the Hong Kong Forum. He is a globally recognized authority on mergers, acquisitions, and negotiations. Carmen G. Cantor, of Puerto Rico, is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Federated States of Micronesia. Cantor is currently the Director of Civil Service Human Resource Management at the Department of State. Lisa W. Hershman, of Indiana, is nominated to be the Chief Management Officer of the Department of Defense. Hershman is currently the Deputy Chief Management Officer and Performing the Duties of the Chief Management Officer of the Department of Defense.